level.code:
int main {
	Variables are how you store information in a program.
	You have to label what TYPE of variable it is before you use it.
	INTEGER variables store positive or negative numbers.
	int current_year = 2019;
	int refers to the type (integer)
	current_year is the name of the variable; that's how we reference it later
	2019 is the value of the variable
	Variables stay in memory until they are changed.
	You can reference the variables later using their names.
	When you run the code, you can print out those variables using COUT
	cout << current_year;
}
